  "general_provisions": "This bill modifies provisions related to the property tax exemption process.",
  "hilighted_provisions": "This bill:<hr><ltbullet>defines terms;<hr><ltbullet>establishes deadlines for:<hr><ltbullet1>a property owner to file an application with the county board of equalization for a property tax exemption; and<hr><ltbullet1>the county board of equalization to render a written decision on an application for a property tax exemption;<hr><ltbullet>authorizes the county board of equalization to request additional information from an applicant for a property tax exemption, in addition to or in lieu of holding a hearing on the application;<hr><ltbullet>provides for the county board of equalization to revoke a property tax exemption if property no longer qualifies for an exemption;<hr><ltbullet>requires the county board of equalization to include notice of a property owner's appeal rights in a written decision regarding a property tax exemption; and<hr><ltbullet>makes technical and conforming changes.",
  "monies": "None",
